{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #208: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $s_1<s_2<\\cdots$ be the sequence of squarefree numbers. Is it true that, for any $\\epsilon>0$ and large $n$,\\[s_{n+1}-s_n \\ll_\\epsilon s_n^{\\epsilon}?\\]Is it true that\\[s_{n+1}-s_n \\leq (1+o(1))\\frac{\\pi^2}{6}\\frac{\\log s_n}{\\log\\log s_n}?\\] Current best: Erd\\H{o}s \\cite{Er51} showed that there are infinitely many $n$ such that\\[s_{n+1}-s_n > (1+o(1))\\frac{\\pi^2}{6}\\frac{\\log s_n}{\\log\\log s_n},\\]so this bound would be the best possible. Filaseta and Trifonov \\cite{FiTr92} proved an upper bound of $s_n^{1/5+o(1)}$. Prize: no. OEIS: A005117, A076259. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_578927dba3747e52","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos208.erdos_208.variants.log_bound https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos208.erdos_208.variants.log_bound.","id":"vf_d7a229622a6ab610","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/208.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_578927dba3747e52","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:208","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_d7a229622a6ab610","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:208","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_d7a229622a6ab610","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce88